Duduzane Zuma is appearing in the Randburg Magistrate’s Court this morning. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma's son Duduzane is appearing in the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Wednesday. WATCH: Pensioner claims Duduzane was speeding His defence team is expected to state his side of the case regarding one count of culpable homicide and one count of reckless and negligent driving. READ: Zuma in court to support Duduzane  Zuma's lawyers argue that the state has failed to prove that Zuma was reckless and negligent for causing the death of a taxi passenger. Zuma initially faced two charges of culpable homicide and a count of negligent driving relating to a car crash on the M1 highway on the 1st of February 2014. 